popt4jlib

Interface ImmigrationIslandOpIntf

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    RandomImmigrationIslandSelector

    public interface ImmigrationIslandOpIntf
extends java.io.Serializable
    interface that may be used in island models of population-based optimization meta-heuristics, allowing for the customization of the island migration topologies. Extends the java.io.Serializable interface so that implementing objects can be transported across JVMs in distributed computation.

    Title: popt4jlib

    Description: A Parallel Meta-Heuristic Optimization Library in Java

      • getImmigrationIsland

        int getImmigrationIsland(int myid,
                         int gen,
                         int[] islandsPop,
                         java.util.HashMap params)
        get the id of the island to which the island with id=myid should send immigrants.
        Parameters:
        myid - int
        gen - int
        islandsPop - int[]
        params - HashMap
        Returns:
        int should be a number in [0, islandsPop.length-1] or -1 to indicate no migration from island with id=myid.
